{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"hasAccess": false, "showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a6d417cc3fb48d67a1c", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "62c481f001514d218a7934d5", "title": "JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "type": "numerical", "level": 3, "approximateTimeRequired": 150, "question": {"text": "<p>A light ray is incident, at an incident angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>, on the system of two plane mirrors <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> having an inclination angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>75</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math> between them (as shown in figure). After reflecting from mirror <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> it gets reflected back by the mirror <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> with an angle of reflection <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>. The total deviation of the ray will be _____ degree.</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/932045b2-6633-43c7-84f1-b1d130c7c9c9-image.png\" style=\"width: 230px; height: 164px;\" /></p>", "image": null}, "options": [], "correctValue": "210", "solution": {"text": "<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/1ced8c4d-3d54-4d94-9578-80649dc04aed-image.png\" style=\"width: 240px; height: 176px;\" /></p><p>From the above figure,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>i</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>,</p><p>Now,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>R</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>180</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>180</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>In triangle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>O</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math>,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>180</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>180</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>And,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>B</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>I</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>I</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>180</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>i</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>180</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>i</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>Now the total deviation of the ray will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#948;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>360</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>i</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>i</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#948;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>360</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfenced><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mi>&#948;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>210</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": {"videoId": "4d92cba349c4460d95f23cbb60be8091", "provider": "vdocipher", "thumbnailLight": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/0VNDcrfZXsoF7.480.jpeg", "thumbnailDark": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/0VNDcrfZXsoF7.480.jpeg", "premiumModules": [{"premiumModuleId": "6628114842d540dfcb148ecb", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "64c7e8e829737784b294e469", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "6788cc0b2dbc1ecacabb7026", "isFree": false}], "description": "JEE Main"}, "questionLabels": [], "numericalLowerLimit": 210, "numericalUpperLimit": 210, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ76673040", "source": "EM", "bucket": "Must Do Ques (JEE Main) - Any Difficulty", "category": null, "microConcepts": [], "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapter